overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to ensure all acceptance criteria were met. The agent
  conducted a detailed analysis of the existing codebase against the provided
  specification, identifying several critical gaps. Subsequently, the agent
  systematically implemented these missing features. This included adding a 1-10
  severity scale for tiredness with crucial safety warnings, integrating
  detection and tailored recommendations for complex sleep disorders like COMISA
  (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and
  implementing a weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS).
  Furthermore, the CSV export functionality was expanded to capture all
  questionnaire responses, and new sections for pain severity and chronic
  fatigue screening were introduced, complete with diagnostic logic and
  guidance. All changes were consistently applied to both the interactive report
  and the downloadable PDF, significantly enhancing the application's diagnostic
  capabilities and user reporting.
